The paper deals with combinatorial group testing schemes, which are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The focus on sparse vectors and disjunctive measurements suggests a connection to compressed sensing (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of randomness condensers and explicit constructions suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC).
